dok raid, where we got wiped on that AoE attempt. here are a few things that I think conrtibuted to the failure ....<br>
<br>
<br>
1. Not everyone had done a &quot;/showspelleffects off&quot; and a &quot;/serverfilter on&quot;. <br>
<br>
This is CRITICAL to assuring that LD's are kept to a minumum. This was the main cause to our only AoE failure in Fear. After EVERYONE had been drilled in turning off all HQ video settings, AND issuing the above commands, AoE went smooth as silk.<br>
<br>
2. A chanter was LD, which left only two chanters to AoE stun. <br>
<br>
Exp for those mobs, there HAS to be an absolute minumum of three chanters (54+) and more if possible. CLerics should NOT have to stun and waste manna which may have to be used for heals.<br>
<br>
3. Positioning around the mobs not the best.<br>
<br>
I went out of the pile to cast a Pillar spell (so I didn't get caught in it also), and it seemed that over half of the circle area of the mobs was open. Chanters and any others that are AoE stunning HAVE to encircle the mob pile so the AoE stun fields overlap and cover ALL the mobs. I really think this wasn't done at that time. I know the I got one PB AoE off (594), then the Pillar spell (895), then got summoned, then got another PB AoE off (594) then was beat on like a snare drum during a rendition of &quot;Wipeout&quot;  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
4. There were three Wizzards, and perhaps 5 druids<br>
<br>
I would say this is the absolute minimum to attempt AoE in Chardok. The more Wizards the better of course (AoE IS our class defining attribute and the reason that Verant considers the Wizard class not to be &quot;underpowered&quot;) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
Thoughts?<br>
<br>
<br>
Afwan<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/umullzy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mullzy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Councilman</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/17/01 2:21:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chardok &amp; AoE</span><hr size=1> Thanks for your thoughts Afwan.  Not being able to stun or AoE I don't have much to add on tactics.  I will eventually have an AoE slow spell (50% slow - not sure, but probably to 4 mobs) so a couple shammies doing that isn't going to hurt the over all effort either.<br>
<br>
Obviously we have a lot to learn about AoE in a dungeon (we got Fear figured out after a couple runs but an outside zone is probably a lot easier) but I can see where it could be a huge asset in Chardok.  We often get accidental agro that could be nicely dealt with if we could switch ot AoE on the fly (not sure if this is practical to do).<br>
<br>
Keep the thoughts coming in... Chardok is still taking a nasty bite out of us every time it seems. <p><p align="center"><strong><font size="2" face="Arial">Mullzy &lt;Infinitus Vindicat&gt; ~
Shaman 55</font><br>
</strong><img src="http://www.telusplanet.net/public/rmulzet/eq/mullet.jpg" width="315"
height="14"> </p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uafwaneq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Afwan EQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/17/01 2:52:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Chardok &amp; AoE</span><hr size=1> Yea, when the king and crew aggroed, if we could have switched to AoE we could have taken the followers out at least, and just had the King to deal with ( if in fact he didn't get hit a few times on the way).<br>
<br>
I really think it would be a good idea to take an evening and go to Chardok and practice some AoE at the upper zoneout area. Get everyone used to the idea, and tactics. If something goes wrong there, it's not that hard to do rezzes and go at it again, if not just zone out quick. PLUS, we can all get good exp from it also <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If we get real good at AoE on the fly I believe it will go a long way to saving our collective butts from time consuming and expensive CR's down the road.<br>
<br>
<br>
Afwan<br>
